  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Development, Support and Improvement of Agricultural Production in Zabre</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">- Training of producers
- Implementation and conduct of Farmer Field Schools by endogenous animators in collective fields
- Guided tours of conduct in Farmers Field Schools
- Participation in outreach radio programs
- Facilitating producer access to equipment and materials for production and post production
- Training women on maintenance and management of the group equipment
- The financial capacity of member producers increased UDGPMZ
- Social mobilization and information meetings outreach groups in each village and social mobilization on the cooperative spirit</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Farmers (men and women)</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Strengthen farmer livelihoods through agricultural production and empowering women. The purpose of this project is to contribute to sustainable improvement of the living conditions of households in the project area through the diversification of agricultural production with emphasis on food crops such as sorghum, cowpea and peanut as well as empowering women.
Objective 1: Increase the farm productivity of households in the project zone. 
Objective 2: Strengthen the capacity of the Departmental Union corn Producer Group Department Zabr&#xE9; (UDGPMZ) to manage and deliver quality services to its members</narrative>
  </description>
